HEADWORD: Discontinuee
<hw>Dis`con*tin`u*ee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>One whose possession of an estate is broken off, or discontinued;
one whose estate is subject to discontinuance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

